contents.name: GENE
contents.description: A region of DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid) coding either for the messenger RNA encoding the amino acid sequence in a polypeptide chain or for a functional RNA molecule. source

contents.name: ALLELE
contents.description: An allele is a variant form of a gene. Some genes have a variety of different forms, which are located at the same position, or genetic locus, on a chromosome. source  source

contents.name: GENOTYPE
contents.description: The term can be used to refer to the alleles, or variant forms of a gene, that are carried by an organism. source

contents.name: PHENOTYPE
contents.description: The term "phenotype" refers to the observable physical properties of an organism; these include the organism's appearance, development, and behavior. An organism's phenotype is determined by its genotype, which is the set of genes the organism carries, as well as by environmental influences upon these genes. source

contents.name: contributes_to
contents.description: Strong association with disease as it is known that mutations in this gene causes the disease.
